<div id="review_44390008" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/44390008" />
    <a title="Andrew" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/913479-andrew"><img alt="Andrew" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1214853875p2/913479.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/44390008?book_show_action=true">Jan 26, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Andrew" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Andrew" href="/user/show/913479-andrew">Andrew</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/913479-andrew?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/913479-andrew?shelf=high-fantasy">high-fantasy</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer44390008&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer44390008" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8326658112835161619">I honestly made it only halfway through the book before I had to put it down. The story was dragging on by the time I put it down. I already could tell that things like the marriage would not take place for a very long time. The return of Darken Raul I thought to be kind of lame. It seems the author is already trying to milk the story for more books, rather than push a stronger plot.<br/><br/>The final straw was the grotesque perverse explicit sex. I thought form reading the first that I could see where G</span>
  <span id="freeText8326658112835161619" style="display:none">I honestly made it only halfway through the book before I had to put it down. The story was dragging on by the time I put it down. I already could tell that things like the marriage would not take place for a very long time. The return of Darken Raul I thought to be kind of lame. It seems the author is already trying to milk the story for more books, rather than push a stronger plot.<br /><br />The final straw was the grotesque perverse explicit sex. I thought form reading the first that I could see where Goodkind was drawing the line at what he would put in the book. I was regretfully very wrong. I did find the irony funny that Goodkind goes to the trouble to create fake vulgarity, not even showing all of it, then goes on to show scenes of such perversion as to offend anyone with decency. I'm sure that as an author he views it his mission to offend everyone he can, and he has succeeded with this reader at least.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8326658112835161619" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


