    <a title="Katherine " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/68791099-katherine"><img alt="Katherine " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1504607541p2/68791099.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2688563264?book_show_action=true">Mar 31, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Katherine " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Katherine " href="/user/show/68791099-katherine">Katherine </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/25812637-stone-of-tears">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/68791099-katherine?shelf=i-died-and-went-to-book-heaven">i-died-and-went-to-book-heaven</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/68791099-katherine?shelf=cant-put-down">cant-put-down</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/68791099-katherine?shelf=shut-up-and-take-my-money">shut-up-and-take-my-money</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/68791099-katherine?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/68791099-katherine?shelf=i-feel-things">i-feel-things</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/68791099-katherine?shelf=epic">epic</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/68791099-katherine?shelf=great-meaning">great-meaning</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/68791099-katherine?shelf=epic-love">epic-love</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/68791099-katherine?shelf=epic-battles">epic-battles</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/68791099-katherine?shelf=genius">genius</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2688563264" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17205225917417780557"><b>ThIS.IS.FANTASY</b>.<br/><br/><img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1554133226ra/27299793.gif' width='' height='' alt='description' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/>This series has <b>true evil</b> and <b>true goodness</b>. This has deep magic and war. <br/><br/><b>Finally</b> an author who not only has good ideas but <b>true writing talent</b> putting so many others in their tiny places. <br/><br/>Fuck best sellers with nothing inside I could read <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/3441.Terry_Goodkind' title='Terry Goodkind' rel='nofollow noopener'>Terry Goodkind</a> <b>all day</b>. <br/><br/>Again I feel like my brain grew some new smart cells while reading this. He is so skilled at describing the mental state and progress of his characters and has the most scintillating dialogues. Not to mention how much ph</span>
  <span id="freeText17205225917417780557" style="display:none"><b>ThIS.IS.FANTASY</b>.<br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1554133226ra/27299793.gif" width="" height="" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>This series has <b>true evil</b> and <b>true goodness</b>. This has deep magic and war. <br><br><b>Finally</b> an author who not only has good ideas but <b>true writing talent</b> putting so many others in their tiny places. <br><br>Fuck best sellers with nothing inside I could read <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/3441.Terry_Goodkind" title="Terry Goodkind" rel="nofollow noopener">Terry Goodkind</a> <b>all day</b>. <br><br>Again I feel like my brain grew some new smart cells while reading this. He is so skilled at describing the mental state and progress of his characters and has the most scintillating dialogues. Not to mention how much philosophy is in this book. <br><br><b>The plot</b> was much different from the first book and gave us the opportunity to really study the personalities of each character on an individual level. <br><br><b>Richard</b> had to use his head like no other and was so wickedly smart throughout the whole book. He’s growing in wisdom and magic and I cannot begin to imagine what he will do in the next books. Also he's shedding some of that babyness and innocence while remaining a good person and I love it. <br><br>He made some very interesting friends that I’m very excited about. Also Nathan. Holly shit, I don’t know if I want him out or in or alive or dead, this is so deliciously mysterious!<br><br>While I am on his squad I have to take a moment to talk about the Gar. The cuteness relief was perfect and the moral lesson from it was perfect as well. <br><br>When it comes to <b>Kahlan</b> I have to correct myself from my review of the first book because she is not “<i>one of the most hard core</i>” she <b>is</b> the most hard core female character. <br><br>Forget the confessors magic, put it completely aside because what she did for and during that battle put to shame so many others and showed us the mastery of <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/3441.Terry_Goodkind" title="Terry Goodkind" rel="nofollow noopener">Terry Goodkind</a>. The tactics, the emotions, the execution down to the last moment were impeccably done. This has to be <b>one of my favorite battles of all time</b>.<br><br>And then to go from that to the rest of things she had to face, I crown her the <b>ultimate braveheart crown</b>. <br><br>Even though the book was even bigger than the first, again I never felt for one second that a single sentence was not needed. <br><br>This is a series for those who <b>truly enjoy world building</b>. <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/3441.Terry_Goodkind" title="Terry Goodkind" rel="nofollow noopener">Terry Goodkind</a> goes into detail about many different peoples of his world, he tells us their customs, their traditions, he wants us to understand the differences they have with each other as well as their histories. <br><br>This is not a romance masqueraded in swords and wanna be assasins and stupid snowflakes. <br><br>This is some real shit. <br></span>
  <a data-text-id="17205225917417780557" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


